/* Shot framed tight around the sides of the long-house. Brebeuf walks into frame and through the curtain. As he crosses the threshold, the exterior lights go down and interior lights come up - silkscreen effect into the building. */

CANCERMAN
(haltingly)
I wore wampum beaded with stars and sat at the head of a feast. The great Huron spirit came. He sat with me and saw the glory of our feast and was pleased... All our ancestor spirits circled around him as he came, whispering the great stories of the Huron...remembering the strength of our nation. 